President Obama has announced the appointment of H.T. Nguyen and Martha G. Abbott to key administration posts. H.T. Nguyen has been appointed as a member of the National Council on Federal Labor-Management Relations. He has been serving as the Executive Director/General Counsel for the Federal Education Association since 1998. Previously, Nguyen held the position of Deputy General Counsel for the FEA from 1988 to 1998. Martha G. Abbott has been appointed as a member of the National Security Education Board. She is currently the Executive Director of the American Council on the Teaching of Foreign Languages and has held this position since 2011. Abbott has also served as the Director of Education at ACTFL from 2004 to 2011 and held various teaching positions earlier in her career.